text: Elizabeth II (born 1926) has been Queen of the United Kingdom and the other Commonwealth realms since 1952. Elizabeth II may also refer to: * Elisabeth II, Abbess of Quedlinburg (1542–1584), Princess-Abbess of Quedlinburg * Queen Elizabeth 2, an ocean liner * Queen Elizabeth II (painting), a painting by Henry Ward ==See also== * List of things named after Elizabeth II * QE2 (disambiguation) *
title: Elizabeth II (disambiguation)
